00:22:45.390 --> 00:22:47.640
you need a cost function,
and you need the number

00:22:47.640 --> 00:22:49.350
of firms in the market.

00:22:49.350 --> 00:22:50.492
You need a demand curve.

00:22:50.492 --> 00:22:52.200
You need the cost
function and the number

00:22:52.200 --> 00:22:53.340
of firms in the market.

00:22:53.340 --> 00:22:56.490
Given that, you can solve
